==English==

===Etymology===
From {{term|Utopia}}, the name of a fictional island, possessing a seemingly perfect socio-politico-legal system in the book ''Utopia'' (1516) by [[w:Thomas More|Sir Thomas More]]. Coined from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|οὐ|tr=ou||not, no|lang=grc}} + {{term|τόπος|tr=topos||place, region|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/juˈtəʊpɪə/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/juˈtoʊpiə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[world]] in which everything and everyone works in perfect [[harmony]].

